<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idb50f3213-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d" identifier="/us/usc/t6/s321h"><num value="321h">§ 321h.</num><heading> Use of national private sector networks in emergency response</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">To the maximum extent practicable, the Secretary shall use national private sector networks and infrastructure for emergency response to chemical, biological, radiological, nuclear, or explosive disasters, and other major disasters.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idb50f3214-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d">(<ref href="/us/pl/107/296/tV/s519">Pub. L. 107–296, title V, § 519</ref>, formerly § 508, <date date="2002-11-25">Nov. 25, 2002</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/116/2215">116 Stat. 2215</ref>; renumbered § 519, <ref href="/us/pl/109/295/tVI/s611/6">Pub. L. 109–295, title VI, § 611(6)</ref>, <date date="2006-10-04">Oct. 4, 2006</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/120/1395">120 Stat. 1395</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idb50f3215-47c4-11f1-9665-b3e99855dc0d">
